<br>
Stamina gives you more hitpoints, but the difference is not that great until high levels.  True, it is the hardest stat to raise through items, but unless you're going to be twinked or Powerleveled, then I would suggest putting most of your points into wisdom, as it will make the journey to higher levels easier, particularly if you are new to the game or to the class.<br>
<br>
If, however, you have a high level character and will be twinking this new guy, definitely STA all the way.<br>
<br>
My 2cp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ujatarus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jatarus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Prince</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/4/02 8:01:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1745.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>   Recommended beastlord starting stats</span><hr size=1>  It pretty much depends on the player and if your are in a guild or even a higher end guild for that matter.<br>
 As a Vah Shir i put all points into wisdom and im finding this out to have worked extremely well for me in my case, but my guild also does higher end raids, short of VT so far, were on emp status in ssra currently.<br>
 As far as the higher end gear and mind you im very picky about what im looking for, but i have found out alot of the stuff has a buttload of stamina on the stats in ssra especially and hps.<br>
 I myself have never played pet cleric, found that would be boring, instead i fight along side my pet all the time and take the beating, i sunk mine into wisdom because alot of the stuff i wanted had sta,str,dex,agi stats as well as really nice AC.<br>
 As i noted above, it pretty much depends on if your in a guild, what your going to be raiding at the higher end of the game as well as your play style. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1745.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1745.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1745.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.brentcopeland.com/beastlord/images/messageboard/BL_add_reply2.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=1745.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.threadControl?topicID=1745.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1745.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1745.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub115.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqbeastlordfrm1">The Den<option value="eqbeastlordfrm2">General Spell Discussion<option value="eqbeastlordfrm3